# RHOAI Newsletter Generator - AI Instructions

This project generates HTML email newsletters from markdown content for the Red Hat OpenShift AI (RHOAI) Dashboard team.

## ‚ö†Ô∏è CRITICAL: Gmail Compatibility Requirements

**ALL generated HTML must be Gmail-compatible. This means:**

### Allowed in Gmail:
- ‚úÖ Inline CSS only (style="..." attributes)
- ‚úÖ Table-based layouts (no flexbox, no CSS grid)
- ‚úÖ Web-safe fonts: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, Georgia, Times New Roman, Courier
- ‚úÖ Basic HTML tags: `<table>`, `<tr>`, `<td>`, `<p>`, `<h1-h6>`, `<a>`, `<img>`, `<span>`, `<center>`
- ‚úÖ HTTPS image URLs (publicly accessible - imgur.com recommended)
- ‚úÖ Background colors via inline styles AND bgcolor attribute
- ‚úÖ Simple CSS properties: color, font-size, padding, margin, background, border, text-align, line-height

### Forbidden in Gmail:
- ‚ùå External CSS files (`<link rel="stylesheet">`)
- ‚ùå `<style>` tags in `<head>`
- ‚ùå JavaScript (any `<script>` tags)
- ‚ùå Forms (`<form>`, `<input>`, `<button>`)
- ‚ùå Video/audio tags (`<video>`, `<audio>`)
- ‚ùå CSS animations or transitions
- ‚ùå Flexbox or CSS Grid
- ‚ùå Position: absolute/fixed
- ‚ùå CSS pseudo-elements (::before, ::after)
- ‚ùå Custom fonts (@font-face)
- ‚ùå SVG inline code (use PNG/JPG images instead)
- ‚ùå Local file paths for images

### Gmail Best Practices:
1. **Maximum width: 600px** - Wider emails may be cut off
2. **Use `<center>` tags** - Gmail sometimes strips CSS centering
3. **Double-specify colors** - Use both `bgcolor="..."` and `style="background:..."`
4. **Test in Gmail** - Always test before sending
5. **Mobile-first** - Use `width:100%` and `max-width` for responsive images
6. **Avoid nested tables >3 levels deep** - Gmail rendering issues
7. **All images must be HTTPS** - HTTP images will be blocked

